Key Match Events: Oliver Baumann’s key save on Xavi’s long range effort in final ten minutes of the game edges him ahead of Alex Nübel’s performance on Friday.
Leweling makes it 1-0 in the 63rd minute.
Leweling’s goal ruled offside by VAR in the 5th minute.
Pre-Game Insights: Germany faced the Netherlands at the Allianz Arena with a long list of injuries.
New faces in midfield with Angelo Stiller and Aleksandar Pavlović, while Deniz Undav was replaced with Leweling.
The last time these two sides met, it ended 2-2 at the Amsterdam Arena.
Post-Match Reflections: This game was a masterclass by Julian Nagelsmann despite missing many first team players.
Germany hardly allowed the Netherlands a shot on goal, showing a dominant performance.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match took place at the Allianz Arena, Munich, Germany.
The game had 75,000 home fans cheering the team on.
